<br>
Boomer has a moment of silence.  He looks around the room and sees the eight foot tall stack of empty pizza boxes, the leather sofas that have been torn to shreds, broken glass, two people passed out in their own vomit, and other atrocities too awful to mention.  To top it all off, someone spray painted “JAMES is a FAG.” Over his ceiling mural.<br>
<br>
Boomers eyes widen.  He looks back to the man sitting on the floor near the doorway.  Boomer speaks slowly and clearly over the mild music “Do you know what day it is?”<br>
<br>
The man stares at him blankly for a moment. “Ummm… what?”<br>
<br>
“Do you know what fucking day it is?”<br>
<br>
“Ummm…wait…what?”<br>
<br>
Boomer flips out, grabs the man by his collar and lifts him up off the ground in an instant, and holds him five inches from his face.  “DO YOU FUCKING KNOW WHAT FUCKING DAY IT IS!?!  How fucking hard is that!?!  Answer the fucking question!  Give me the date, the day of the week, anything!”<br>
<br>
At this point everyone who is conscious has their attention towards Boomer.<br>
<br>
The man speaks up, a bit snappier this time. “Uh, the fifteenth?”<br>
<br>
“Of what month?”<br>
<br>
“Umm…what?”<br>
<br>
Boomer pulls out his gun and slams it on the mans face, breaking his nose.  “Go on, say WHAT again Mother Fucker, say WHAT again!”<br>
<br>
“Uh, July!  It’s July!”<br>
<br>
“Good…good.  You got the right fucking month.  That’s a start.  Now, do you remember the day that you sent all of the straight edge people upstairs?”<br>
<br>
“Yeah.  Fuck man, I can’t feel my face.”<br>
<br>
“Hey, focus.  Now, do you remember how long you were supposed to be doing that for?”<br>
<br>
“Wh-what?”<br>
<br>
Boomer knees him in the groin, then holds him up off the ground.  “DO YOU KNOW WHO I AM, MOTHER FUCKER?”<br>
<br>
The man glances around the room to see if anyone is going to mouth him the name of the person who is beating the living crap out of him at that very moment, but everyone is just sitting there dumbfounded.  After a few seconds the man just guesses. “Uh, James?” <br>
<br>
Without hesitation Boomer hits the man with lightning speed and sends him flying across the room and crashing through a table.  The man is completely knocked out.<br>
<br>
Boomer walks upstairs, unlocks his bedroom, and grabs a huge CD case and a crate of records before locking up and walking back downstairs.  “Hey, you!  What’s your name?”<br>
<br>
“B-B-Brian.”<br>
<br>
“You’re in charge Brian, make sure that this place gets cleaned up before I get back, or there will be fucking hell to pay…. Oh, yes, and Brian?”<br>
<br>
“Yeah?”<br>
<br>
“There’s a package arriving in three days for you, so long as you drop that punk ass mother fucker off at rehab tonight.  Peace, I’m out.”<br>
<br>
And Boomer exits, leaving the room full of people in complete astonishment.<br>
<br>
As Boomer walks down his driveway, he mumbles to himself “Well, that was fun.  What can I say, I’m a busy guy with shit to do.”<br>
